charles osgood wood, iii (born january 8, 1933), known professionally as charles osgood, is an american radio and television commentator and writer. his daily program, the osgood file, has been broadcast on the cbs radio network since 1971. osgood is best known for being the host of cbs news sunday morning, a role he held from april 10, 1994 until september 25, 2016. he is also known for being the voice of the narrator of horton hears a who!, an animated film released in 2008, based on the book of the same name by dr. seuss. he published a memoir of his boyhood in 2004. on august 28, 2016, osgood formally announced his retirement from cbs news sunday morning, with his final appearance airing on september 25.